content: standujar: This week, standujar drove significant feature development, most notably implementing a unified messaging API (`eliza#6095`) and adding critical multi-tenancy support with PostgreSQL Row-Level Security in `eliza#6101`, a complex change with over 2700 lines added. They also shipped several important bug fixes for server stability and agent persistence (`eliza#6105`, `eliza#6106`) and enhanced the Solana plugin with wallet improvements (`plugin-solana#21`). Their work shows a primary focus on new feature implementation, complemented by refactoring and bug fixes across the codebase.
